actions.comment:
Thanks for reporting this. The freeze is likely caused by `SKGLSurfaceViewRenderer.OnSurfaceCreated` not resetting the Skia `GRContext` when Android recreates the EGL context after a background/foreground transition. The sibling `SKGLTextureViewRenderer` handles this correctly by calling `FreeContext()` in the same callback.

As a workaround, try calling `OnPause()` and `OnResume()` on your `SKGLSurfaceView` from the hosting Fragment or Activity lifecycle:

```csharp
protected override void OnPause()
{
    base.OnPause();
    skglSurfaceView.OnPause();
}

protected override void OnResume()
{
    base.OnResume();
    skglSurfaceView.OnResume();
}
```

Alternatively, if GPU acceleration isn't critical, switching to `SKCanvasView` (CPU rendering) avoids the EGL lifecycle entirely.

Would you be able to confirm whether the `OnPause`/`OnResume` workaround resolves the freeze?
